  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink270-kilavi">varaivu kāraṇamāka neṭṭiṭai kaḻintu poruḷvayiṟ pōkiya talaimakaṉ vantamai yaṟinta tōḻi yuvanta vuḷḷattaḷāyt talaimakaṭkuc colliyatu. 
          </p>
        <p xml:lang="en"> What the confidante, knowing that the hero—who had gone away for the sake of wealth—had returned after a long interval for the sake of marriage, said to the heroine, being inwardly glad.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink270">
<l>kiḻaṅkakaḻ kēḻa luḻuta cilampiṟ</l>
<l>ṟalaiviḷai kāṉavar koytaṉar peyarum</l>
<l>pulleṉ kuṉṟattup pulampuko ṇeṭuvarai</l>
<l>kāṇiṉuṅ kaliḻunōy cettut</l>
<l>tāmvan taṉarnaṅ kāta lōrē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>Thinking of the pain in which [you] cry,</l>
        <l>even if you see the tall mountain range</l>
        <l>that takes on loneliness,</l>
        <l>with lacklustre hills where forest people</l>
        <l>leave, having plucked the first harvest </l>
        <l rend="indent2">on the mountain slope ploughed </l>
        <l rend="indent2">by boars that dig up bulbous roots—</l>
        <l>our lover came.</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
